Here are basic networking interview questions explained in a simple, real-time way (useful for DevOps interviews too):

🔹 1. What is Networking?
👉 Networking means connecting multiple computers or devices to share data.

Real-time example:
Office systems connected to the same Wi-Fi to share files or access the internet.

🔹 2. What is an IP Address?
👉 A unique number given to each device in a network.

Example:
192.168.1.1

📌 Like your home address → helps identify your device.

🔹 3. What is DNS?
👉 DNS converts domain names into IP addresses.

Example:
google.com → 142.250.183.206

📌 Without DNS, you must remember IPs for every website.

🔹 4. What is a Subnet?
👉 A smaller network inside a big network.

Why used?

Better management

Improved security

🔹 5. What is a Gateway?
👉 The device that connects your network to another network.

Example:
Your router connects your home network to the internet.

🔹 6. What is HTTP vs HTTPS?
HTTP	HTTPS
Not secure	Secure
No encryption	Encrypted
Port 80	Port 443
📌 Always prefer HTTPS in real-world apps.

🔹 7. What is TCP vs UDP?
TCP	UDP
Reliable	Fast but unreliable
Connection-oriented	Connectionless
Used in websites	Used in streaming/gaming
🔹 8. What is a Port?
👉 A communication endpoint for applications.

Examples:

80 → HTTP

443 → HTTPS

22 → SSH

🔹 9. What is a Firewall?
👉 A security system that controls incoming/outgoing traffic.

Real-time:
Blocks unauthorized access to your server.

🔹 10. What is NAT?
👉 Network Address Translation converts private IP to public IP.

📌 Used in routers to allow multiple devices to use one internet connection.

🔹 11. What is DHCP?
👉 Automatically assigns IP addresses to devices.

📌 Example: When you connect to Wi-Fi, IP is given automatically.

🔹 12. What is Ping?
👉 Used to check if a server is reachable.

ping google.com
🔹 13. What is OSI Model?
👉 7-layer model to understand networking.

Layers:

Physical

Data Link

Network

Transport

Session

Presentation

Application

📌 Interview tip: Remember "All People Seem To Need Data Processing"

🔹 14. What is MAC Address?
👉 Unique hardware address of a device.

📌 Example: 00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E

🔹 15. What is Bandwidth?
👉 Amount of data transferred per second.

📌 Example: 100 Mbps internet speed

🔥 Interview Tip (Important for You – DevOps)
If interviewer asks:

👉 “Website not opening, what will you check?”

Answer like this:

Check internet / ping

Check DNS resolution

Check server status

Check ports (80/443)

Check firewall rules

