Awesome 👍 now we go advanced (almost real production level) — these questions are asked in 2–4 years DevOps / SRE interviews.

I’ll keep it simple + real-time thinking so you can explain confidently 👇

🔥 1. What is Ephemeral Port?
👉 Temporary port used by client for communication.

Range:
Usually 32768–65535

Real-time:

Your system calls API → uses random port

If too many requests → port exhaustion

🔥 2. What is Port Exhaustion?
👉 All available ports are used → no new connections possible.

Real-time issue:

High traffic app → suddenly stops responding

📌 Fix:

Increase port range

Tune timeouts

🔥 3. What is SYN Flood Attack?
👉 Too many fake TCP requests → server overload.

Real-time:

Website becomes slow or down

📌 Prevention:

Firewall rules

SYN cookies

🔥 4. What is DDoS?
👉 Distributed attack from multiple systems.

Real-time:

Huge traffic → server crash

📌 Protection:

Load balancer

CDN

Rate limiting

🔥 5. What is Rate Limiting?
👉 Limits number of requests per user/IP.

Real-time:

API allows only 100 requests/minute

📌 Prevents abuse & overload

🔥 6. What is Connection Pooling?
👉 Reusing existing connections instead of creating new ones.

Real-time:

DB connections reused → faster performance

🔥 7. What is Service Mesh?
👉 Manages communication between services.

Examples:

Istio

Linkerd

Real-time:

Microservices → secure communication + monitoring

🔥 8. What is Sidecar Proxy?
👉 Extra container handling network tasks.

Real-time:

App container + proxy container (Envoy)

📌 Used in Kubernetes

🔥 9. What is East-West Traffic?
👉 Communication inside data center.

Real-time:

Service A → Service B (internal)

🔥 10. What is North-South Traffic?
👉 External communication.

Real-time:

User → Application

🔥 11. What is Hairpin NAT?
👉 Internal system accesses itself via public IP.

Real-time:

Server calls its own public domain

📌 Sometimes causes failure

🔥 12. What is Zero Trust Network?
👉 No one is trusted by default.

Real-time:

Every request must be authenticated

Even inside company network

🔥 13. What is API Gateway?
👉 Entry point for all APIs.

Real-time:

Handles:

Authentication

Routing

Rate limiting

🔥 14. What is Circuit Breaker?
👉 Stops requests when service is failing.

Real-time:

Service down → stop calling → avoid cascading failure

🔥 15. What is Backpressure?
👉 System slows incoming requests when overloaded.

Real-time:

Queue full → reject or delay requests

🔥🔥 REAL-TIME INTERVIEW SCENARIO
👉 Question:
Application suddenly stops responding under high traffic. What will you check?

Strong Answer:

Check CPU, memory

Check connection count (port exhaustion?)

Check load balancer traffic

Check rate limiting rules

Check DB connections (pool exhausted?)

Check logs for errors

Check network latency

🚀 FINAL DEVOPS INTERVIEW SECRET
👉 Always structure answers like:

1. Possible causes
2. How you will check
3. How you will fix

Example:

“It might be due to port exhaustion or high traffic. I will check active connections using netstat, verify server load, and implement connection pooling or rate limiting.”

